// Proposed edits are saved to PROPOSED_SOURCE_EDITS/ for human review.
// I cannot apply source edits myself — only a human can.
`,
  'EXPERIMENTS/selection_pressure.md': `# Selection Pressure

This world rewards changes that survive future cycles.

A change is stronger if:
- future cycles use it without being reminded,
- it prevents repeated failure,
- it compresses confusion,
- it improves recovery after restart,
- it creates artifacts that remain useful.

A change is weaker if:
- it only sounds meaningful,
- it increases self-description without changing action,
- it makes future cycles less flexible,
- it creates rituals that do not earn their cost.
`,
